    • equals

      public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object o)
      Description copied from interface: HMap.HEntry
      Compares the specified object with this entry for equality. Returns true if the given object is also a HMap entry and the two entries represent the same mapping. More formally, two entries e1 and e2 represent the same mapping if
           (e1.getKey()==null ?
      e2.getKey()==null : e1.getKey().equals(e2.getKey()))  &&
     (e1.getValue()==null ?
      e2.getValue()==null : e1.getValue().equals(e2.getValue()))
      This ensures that the equals method works properly across different implementations of the HMap.Entry interface.
      Specified by:
      equals in interface HMap.HEntry
      Overrides:
      equals in class java.lang.Object
      Parameters:
      o - object to be compared for equality with this HMap entry
      Returns:
      true if the specified object is equal to this HMap entry

    • hashCode

      public int hashCode()
      Description copied from interface: HMap.HEntry
      Returns the hash code value for this HMap entry. The hash code of a HMap entry e is defined to be: 
           (e.getKey()==null   ? 0 : e.getKey().hashCode()) ^
     (e.getValue()==null ? 0 : e.getValue().hashCode())
      This ensures that e1.equals(e2) implies that e1.hashCode()==e2.hashCode() for any two Entries e1 and e2, as required by the general contract of Object.hashCode.
      Specified by:
      hashCode in interface HMap.HEntry
      Overrides:
      hashCode in class java.lang.Object
      Returns:
      the hash code value for this HMap entry
      See Also:
      Object.hashCode(), Object.equals(Object), HMap.HEntry.equals(Object)
